Dilated bile duct (defined as >6 mm with gallbladder in situ and 8 mm following cholecystectomy) 
and elevated liver enzymes. However, her LFTs (TBil <4) place her in the intermediate risk category 
for choledocholithiasis and she needs additional testing. 
Options include MRI/MRCP, endoscopic ultrasound, and cholecystectomy with interoperative cholangiogram.

